CHAPTER SIXTEEN

851
01:29:51,909 --> 01:29:56,469
Hot and cold, big and small

852
01:29:56,469 --> 01:30:03,320
Florida in the far Southeast is called the
'Sunshine State' because it is so warm and

853
01:30:03,320 --> 01:30:04,320
sunny.

854
01:30:04,320 --> 01:30:09,469
Oranges grow there, and visitors come to enjoy
beach holidays.

855
01:30:09,469 --> 01:30:15,349
They can also visit Walt Disney World and
the Kennedy Space Center.

856
01:30:15,349 --> 01:30:22,659
Florida has the Everglades, an area which
is not like any other place in the USA.

857
01:30:22,659 --> 01:30:30,060
The land is very wet and has many trees, plants,
animals and birds that are not found in other

858
01:30:30,060 --> 01:30:32,840
parts of America.

859
01:30:32,840 --> 01:30:39,340
But Florida is very popular with older people
who want to live somewhere warm.

860
01:30:39,340 --> 01:30:46,579
This means new houses and roads, and building
them has destroyed a lot of the land.

861
01:30:46,579 --> 01:30:52,540
There are also more and more factories, and
some people are angry that this beautiful

862
01:30:52,540 --> 01:31:00,250
state is losing many of its wild birds and
animals because of its dirty air and water.

863
01:31:00,250 --> 01:31:08,639
Cold, lonely Alaska is the largest state in
the USA, and Canada stands between it and

864
01:31:08,639 --> 01:31:10,960
the other states.

865
01:31:10,960 --> 01:31:18,579
Fishing and hunting used to bring money to
Alaska, and gold was found there too.

866
01:31:18,579 --> 01:31:23,230
But today it is important for its oil.

867
01:31:23,230 --> 01:31:31,560
North America's highest mountain, Mount McKinley
(6,194 metres), is in Alaska.

868
01:31:31,560 --> 01:31:37,900
A great way to travel there is by boat from
Seattle.

869
01:31:37,900 --> 01:31:44,760
Most visitors go in summer; in winter it is
very cold, and it is dark for most of the

870
01:31:44,760 --> 01:31:48,469
day because it is so far north.

871
